race.description: The Chop Shop Butchery Mdn Plate
race.comment: INTO BROOKLYN (6) went straight to the front and looked a chance but found one better last start over 1300m at Hawkesbury. Back in trip but she has the speed to cope. Not much depth here so this is a great opportunity to break through. VITTOZZI (11) settled back in the field and was trapped on a limb before a respectable midfield finish first-up over 1100m at Hawkesbury. Nicely drawn and at just her third race start can improve sharply. HEAD KAHUNA (1) is back from a four-month spell. Has only raced once and wasn't far away over this distance at Scone after showing good gate speed. Recent trial winner who just needs luck from a tricky gate to be in the finish. RING MY BELL (8) failed to flatter first-up at Coonabarabran but a better run is on the cards on a nine-day back-up with winkers going on. WHITTELLO SUN (2) trialled well at Scone recently and is worth monitoring on debut.
